Anthony Crolla: Fighter wants world title after fight to get back in ring
Media playback is not supported on this deviceFormer British Lightweight champion Anthony Crolla was a few weeks away from a world title fight when he wasseriously injured chasing burglarsfrom his neighbour's house.Crolla had a concrete slab smashed on his head which fractured his skull and also broke his ankle, putting his title ambitions on hold.After months of tough rehabilitation the 28-year-old is ready to take part in the Great Manchester Run to say thank you to his well-wishers.